<div class="home container" data-controller="scroll">
  <section class="banner" id="seven-continents">
    <% if @photo %>
      <div class="country-banner">
        <%= image_tag(@photo.image_url, alt: "#{@photo.image_alt}", class: "banner-image") %>
        <h1 class="page-header">The Country Club.</h1>
        <div class="banner-image-attributions">
          <p><%= @photo.country.name %></p>
          <p>
            Photo by
            <%= link_to @photo.photographer_name,
                "#{@photo.photographer_url}?utm_source=the_country_club&utm_medium=referral",
                target: '_blank',
                rel: 'noopener',
                class: "photographer-link" %>
            on
            <%= link_to 'Unsplash',
                'https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=the_country_club&utm_medium=referral',
                target: '_blank',
                rel: 'noopener',
                class: "photographer-link" %>
          </p>
        </div>
        <i
          class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down down-arrow fa-bounce"
          style="--fa-bounce-start-scale-x: 1;
                --fa-bounce-height: 10px;
                --fa-bounce-start-scale-y: 1;
                --fa-bounce-jump-scale-x: 1;
                --fa-bounce-jump-scale-y: 1;
                --fa-bounce-land-scale-x: 1;
                --fa-bounce-land-scale-y: 1;
                --fa-bounce-rebound: 0;
                --fa-animation-duration: 2s;"
          data-action="click->scroll#scrollToFirstSection">
        </i>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </section>

  <section class="home-info">
    <div class="top-info-box" data-scroll-target="firstSection">
      <h2 id="home-info-header">A travel tracker. <br> For the curious traveller.</h2>
      <p class="home-info-text">
        As someone who loves travelling and going down geography rabbit holes on Wikipedia, I built this app to
        merge these two interests together. <br>
        Have your favourite countries and countries you want to visit all in one place. <br>
        Be inspired by beautiful photos,
        courtesy of <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=the_country_club&utm_medium=referral" target="_blank">Unsplash</a>,
        and learn more about each country. <br>
        Get suggestions from <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/claude">Claude</a> for activities and recommendations
        for the best time to visit. <br>
        <% if !user_signed_in? %>
          <%= button_to "Join the Club", new_user_registration_path, :method => "get", class: "join-button" %>
        <% end %>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="all-info-box-grid">
      <div class="info-box">
        <div class="info-box-inner">
          <div class="info-box-text">
          <h2>Where Next?</h2>
            <p>
              Discover your next holiday destination. <br>
              Use AI to get activity suggestions and to find out when the best time to go is. <br>
              Choose a country and add it to your wishlist. <br>
              Rank how much you want to visit there. <br>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        <div class="info-box-inner">
          <div class="info-box-text">
          <h2>Relive It.</h2>
            <p>
              Revisit your favourite countries by adding a country to your favourites. <br>
              Keep track of how many times you've visited, and when. <br>
              Add any notes about the country. <br>
              You can even upload any photos from your trip (in development).
            </p>
            <%# link %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        <div class="info-box-inner">
          <div class="info-box-text">
            <h2>Be Curious.</h2>
            <p>
              Learn more about a particular country, as each country page has useful facts and figures. <br>
              Find out its capital and where its located. <br>
              Discover how small or large a country is, in terms of population. <br>
              Get your travel money organised by using the currency exchange tool (in development).
            </p>
            <%= link_to "Visit a random country", country_path(@random_country), class: "web-link" %>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box-container right-image">
            <%= image_tag("/images/be-curious.gif", alt: "gif showing website navigation of country page", class: "home-page-gif") %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        <div class="info-box-inner">
          <div class="info-box-container left-image">
            <%= image_tag("/images/react-weather.gif", alt: "React Weather app gif", class: "home-page-gif") %>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box-text">
            <h2>Be Prepared.</h2>
            <p>
              Use my other app to get the weather and some activity suggestions for a city you're visiting. <br>
              Search for a city (or even an area of a particular city) so that you're prepared for the day, whatever the weather may be. <br>
              If you're stuck for ideas, use AI to get some activity suggestions that are weather-appropriate.
            </p>
            <%= link_to "Visit React Weather", "https://react-weather-claude-app-af1fc23c96a1.herokuapp.com/", target: "_blank", class: "web-link" %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <p>
      All photos from Unsplash. No offence is meant to be caused by any of the photos.
    </p>
  </footer>
</div>
